<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/979> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #979" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Whatever the reasons for this defeat, the fact was accepted by Polybius (2.19.5; cf. Liv. 10.26.7-13)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/978> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #978" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 10.22.9; Elog. 10, CIL 1\n     , p. 192; Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79 and 12. Held command in Etruria till the Consuls came (Liv. 10.24.18-26, an unreliable tale), and after Decius' death served in Campania and Samnium (Liv. 10.31.3-7)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/970> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #970" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 10.15.7-16; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -] Ca[ecus II], [- - - -Vio]lens II); Chr. 354 (Ceco et Violense); Fast. Hyd. (Claudio et Violente; see note); Chr. Pasc. (see note); Cassiod.; cf. on Claudius, Cic. Sen. 16; Elog. 10, CIL 1\n     , p. 192; Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79 and 12. See Degrassi 38f., 111, 426f. Claudius fought Etruscans and Sabelli (Sabini, Elog.) in Etruria, and vowed a temple to Bellona (Liv. 10.18-22; Elog.; Ovid Fast. 6.199-202; Dio fr. 36.27; Auct. Vir. Ill. 34.5). Volumnius served in Samnium and Lucania, returned to give undesired aid to Claudius in Etruria, defeated a Samnite invasion of Campania, and returned to Rome to hold elections (Liv. 10.17-22). On Volumnius, see Lübker no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/969> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #969" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "One annalistic account gave Claudius a share in the campaign in Samnium (Liv. 10.17.13; cf. Elog.); one gave the two Consuls credit for the achievements assigned above to Decius and Fabius; one gave them to Volumnius alone; and others credited Decius only with Murgantia, while Ferentinum and Romulea fell to Fabius (see Proconsuls); Liv. 10.17.11; cf. Dio, who preserves a part of the account of Claudius' unwillingness to accept aid from Volumnius (fr. 36.27). With such a tradition attribution of particular achievements to particular commanders is highly unsafe." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/965> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #965" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 10.22.8 (295 B.C.); Elog. 10, CIL 1\n     , p. 192; Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79 and 12. If his second praetorship falls in 295, 297 is the latest possible date for the first." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/962> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #962" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 10.11.10; and on Claudius, Elog. 10, CIL 1\n     , p. 192; Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79 and 12. See Tribunes of the Plebs." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/923> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #923" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Twice Aed. Cur. (Elog. 10, CIL 1\n     , p. 192, and Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79 and 12). Seidel (11) assumed that he preceded Cn. Flavius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/911> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #911" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 9.42.2; 10.15.12; Diod. 20.45.1; Fast. Cap. (names entire); Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Claudius, Elog. 10 in CIL 1\n     , p. 192, and Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79 and 12; Degrassi 38f., 110, 422f. Volumnius held command against the Sallentini (Liv. 9.42.4-5; cf. Diod. 20.80.1-2, on operations in Iapygia, in 306). Piso omitted this college from his Annals (Liv. 9.44.3-4). On Volumnius, see Lübker no. 3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/899> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #899" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Livy (9.33-34) describes an attempt by Tribunes to compel Claudius to give up office when his colleague did so at the end of the regular term (cf. Liv. 9.29.7-8; Diod. 20.36.6; Auct. Vir. Ill. 34). Mommsen (Str. 2.351, n. 2) believes that extraordinary prorogations to finish such tasks as the Appian Way and the Claudian aqueduct were permitted." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/893> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #893" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The tibicines emigrated to Tibur but were brought back and restored their right of dining on the Capitol (Liv. 9.30.9-10; Val. Max. 2.5.4; Ovid Fasti 6.657-692)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/889> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #889" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 9.29.5; Diod. 20.36.1; Fast. Cap.; Frontin. Aq. 1.5; cf. on Claudius, Elog. 10, CIL 1\n     , p. 192; Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79 and 12; Cic. Sen. 16; Suet. Tib. 1.2; Pompon. in Dig. 1.2.2.36; Fest. 270 L, and texts cited, below; see Degrassi 36f., 110, 420f. Diod. (20.36.1-5) mentions the concord, Livy the disagreement of the Censors (9.29.7, and 33.4) and Plautius' abdication while Claudius continued in office (cf. Frontin. Aq. 1.5; Auct. Vir. Ill. 34; Mommsen, Str. 2.351, note 2). Claudius paved the Appian way to Capua, built the Claudian aqueduct, admitted sons of freedmen to the Senate, and gave landless citizens full citizen rights; also these Censors forbade the tibicines to hold their festival in the temple of Jupiter, and transferred the cult of Hercules at the Ara Maxima from the Potitii to public slaves (Cic. Cael. 34-35; Liv. 9.29.5-11, and 33-34, and 46.10-11; Diod. 20.36.1-6; Elog. above; Ovid Fast. 6.654-692; Val. Max. 1.1.17; 2.5.4; Frontin. Aq. 1.5; Plut. Popl. 7.5; Suet. Claud. 24; Eutrop. 2.9.3; Pomp. Dig. 1.2.2.36; Serv. Aen. 8.179; Lact. Inst. Div. 2.7.15; Jerome Chr. ad ann. 325, p. 125 Helm; Cassiod.; Fest. 270 L; Macrob. Sat. 3.6.13). See 311 and 310. On Plautius, see Lübker no. 19." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8841> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8841" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 725, footnote 5" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/880> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #880" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Held the office twice (Elog. 10, CIL 1\n     , p. 192; Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79; cf. Ovid Fast. 6.663), the first time probably before his censorship in 312." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/863> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #863" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elog. 10 in CIL 1\n     , p. 192; Inscr. Ital. 13.3.79. The date is unknown; this is the latest one probable if he was Curule Aedile before his censorship (Sobeck, Quaest. 5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7788> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7788" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 307, 296. See above, on Q. Aemilius Barbula (33). Cos. 230, for the suggestion that this Claudius was the honorand in the Elogium of Brindisi.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1040> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1040" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elog., CIL 1\n     , p. 192- Inscr. Ital. 13.2.79 and 12." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1038> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1038" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These three dictatorships must be dated after the end of Livy's record in Book 10 in 292, and before 284, when a fragment of Fast. Cap. begins. Mommsen suggested 287 for Claudius after the death of Hortensius, but there is no specific evidence. They are listed above at the latest possible date, 285." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10323> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10323" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/26> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A.25-27 (military tribune three times ca. 312)" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10322> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10322" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
